events.article_title: Gate.io Not Supporting NFTX (NFTX) Token Swap and Initiating a Delisting and Buyback Plan
events.event_summary: Gate.io has suspended the deposit service for NFTX (NFTX).
events.user_action_required: Users cannot deposit NFTX (NFTX) on Gate.io.

events.article_title: Gate.io Not Supporting NFTX (NFTX) Token Swap and Initiating a Delisting and Buyback Plan
events.event_summary: Users holding NFTX (NFTX) on Gate.io after October 1, 2024, can apply for a buyback.
events.user_action_required: Users must fill out the provided form to apply for the buyback between October 1, 2024, 16:00 UTC and October 24, 16:00 UTC.
quantifiable_changes: Buyback price of 2.353 USDT with a maximum compensation limit of 100 USDT per user.

events.article_title: Gate.io Not Supporting NFTX (NFTX) Token Swap and Initiating a Delisting and Buyback Plan
events.event_summary: Gate.io will delist NFTX (NFTX) from the trading market, including NFTX_USDT and NFTX_ETH spot trading pairs, quant grid trading, and liquidity mining.
events.user_action_required: Users should adjust trading strategies and withdraw liquidity before delisting.

events.article_title: Gate.io Not Supporting NFTX (NFTX) Token Swap and Initiating a Delisting and Buyback Plan
events.event_summary: Users with ongoing quant grid trading of NFTX (NFTX) should adjust trading strategies before October 4, 2024, 03:00 UTC.
events.user_action_required: Users should adjust their trading strategies to avoid automatic termination.

events.article_title: Gate.io Not Supporting NFTX (NFTX) Token Swap and Initiating a Delisting and Buyback Plan
events.event_summary: Users who have provided liquidity for NFTX (NFTX) in the liquidity mining market should withdraw liquidity before October 4, 2024, 03:00 UTC.
events.user_action_required: Users should withdraw their liquidity to avoid automatic redemption.
